# This .dockerignore governs the CLIENT image build only: its build context is
# the repository root (see docker-compose*.yml build.context: .) so the Dockerfile
# can COPY both services/client and the repo-root shared/ at build time. The
# server and mongo images build from their own contexts with their own rules.
#
# Strategy: exclude everything, re-include only the client app and shared/, then
# strip dependency trees, build output, and secrets so none ride into a layer.
*
!services
!shared
services/server

**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
**/.env
**/*.env
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.crt
**/certs
